reviews.text: First time ordering from Primo Pizza tonight! I was immediately happy with the kindness of the person that answered the phone (don't know his name, but he was wearing a hat and had a beard lol).... the pizza is delicious and the service was awesome! Definitely adding Primo Pizza to my list of favorites pizzas in the area.

They let me use a coupon by phone that was texted to me since the link didn‚Äôt work. Love their flat bread pizza especially. They usually deliver 10-15 minutes prior to the estimated 45 minutes. And I just found out that their new menu has items not usually found on pizza menus.

Horrible experience I been coming here for many many years. If I could give this place a zero I would. June 18,2025 Wednesday me and my family order a couple pizzas where we paid the driver $31.68 including a tip total it out to $35 which was cash compared to card where you have to sign for it. Later on that night the manager called and try to excuse me of not only stealing pizza but not paying for it. When I have cameras around my house that prove that I went outside and pay cash and the delivery guy put the money into his pocket after he given me the receipt. Again why would anyone place an order and not pay for it I would think the delivery person would have called the store and say the customer didn‚Äôt pay for the food with cash or credit card. Very unprofessional and stereotype why wait until closing to call about a customer didn‚Äôt pay mind you this was 4 hours ago make it make sense. You need to check on your delivery staff who‚Äôs not returning the money at the end of the day or the receipts I would think the delivery person keeps all the receipts from each person and count the money from the deliveries they have done that day.
Again if primo pizza want to be sue for false allegations wrongfully excusing someone for not paying for their pizza order that‚Äôs fine I do have evidences from the receipt I paid cash not credit card along with ring cameras zoom in  showing the delivery guy put the money in his pocket after handing me the pizza. Check your staff not the customers because usually the customers are right not the staff.

[Edit:]

I see the business has replied to my review. I wanted add, yes I did receive a voice-mail.

My issue as to why I did not call back is yes I understand this was an error. What I don't understand is someone clearly took out, saw & placed that pizza(?) into the box and sent it to a customer.

No one said anything until I made a review. Literally minutes after I posted the original review I received the voice-mail, while I was driving to go get something else to eat, btw. I really have no interest in trying a 3rd time, especially with the many poor quality pizza/Italian restaurants within this delivery area. I'm not interested in a refund or anything. Thanks.

[Original Review:]

4.5? This is what I got, a personal pan pizza for $10 plus taxes & delivery fee. Lmmfao I'm guessing most cannot even guess which specialty( special lol) pizza this is. And no, it's not the burnt slop specialty pizza.

I included 2 photos with & without the flash. Doesn't matter it tasted as disgusting as it looks. And went instantly in the trash after one gross bite.

Side Note: do people in CT not know how to actually cut a pizza? Is it that challenging or is it difficult to slice hard chewy gross doe. Hmmm.

I am a very Happy Customer for several years now!

The Service(on the phone) is Great.

The Pizzas are Delicious!

I Highly Recommend Primo Pizza!!

The deal did change recently. It used to be half-price for large pizzas if you go pick it up. The discount is a little less now but still an incredible value. Highly recommended.
